# 🧠 THIS IS THE BIG EVOLUTION

Notice what disappeared:

❌ `type`

That’s intentional.

---

# 🚨 WHY REMOVING `type` IS IMPORTANT

Because node “types” become explosive over time.

Instead, V3 should compose nodes from:

| Concern        | Purpose                        |
| -------------- | ------------------------------ |
| `interaction`  | how player interacts           |
| `presentation` | how content is visually framed |
| `effects`      | runtime mutation               |
| `transitions`  | progression flow               |
| `requirements` | gating                         |
| `assets`       | media                          |
| `tracking`     | progression rules              |

This is dramatically more scalable.

